snippet.textDisplay: As someone who is a barista and also works at a coffee shop that is also a roaster (we roast in house). This is a complete uneducated money scam in my opinion. 5 bags for 10 dollars, but you have to use 3 to make a mason jars worth and would have to buy more to make 2 mason jars full of coffee. Her comment on French presses being hard, it simply is not. If you don’t want to ground your coffee, buy grounded coffee or get it grounded from the place you buy it. Literally add hot water, some coffee grounds, wait a couple minutes to brew and press. Boom you have a whole thing of coffee that will make you 2-4 mason jars of coffee depending on how much creamer/milk you use. I nice bag of small production local roasted bag of beans could cost you anywhere from 9-15 dollars, which will literally make you weeks of coffee. Not just 1 use, oh and don’t forget shipping. She literally said in the video that she only spent a couple hours trying and picking out coffees that were pre-made for her. I’d be less upset about the price point and the concept of the coffee if she actual put in the time to understand more about coffee. I am disappointed that she thinks it’s okay to profit off her younger fans. This is a huge profit for those small bags of coffee that you have to buy multiple packs to even make more than one mason jar of coffee. Even if it’s compostable, what a waste of resources when she literally could have came out with a bag of pre-ground coffee beans and a cute scoop that does that “perfect amount for her coffee recipe”. That in itself would have been impressive and cute. This just simply isn’t. A waste of natural resources and money.
